--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, Yanshosh@a... wrote:
> Hmm.. I guess examples of basic unclassified info would be scan 
results, 
> damage reports, stuff like that.


Lady Hawk dug through the files and found geological scans. fairly 
old but there shouldn't be much of a change from when they were 
taken. She studied the scans trying to find where each of the 
alliance members had landed. Those scans would give her a good idea 
where certain animals would be dominant. "This planet is going 
through changes that Avaria (Her home planet) could never survive." 
She wondered if it was the translife that caused the changes or the 
natural balance of the planet.

She eventually came across a CR report chart. She was headed in the 
right direction. If she had the readouts from the chambers dna 
stabilizers she wouldn't need direct contact with the Alliance 
members. All she'd have to do was have the chamber create a sample 
for her. 

If the chamber could patch the robotics in translife it would also 
have to be able to create compatible genetic material to patch the 
biological side too. If this is a mode let me know and I'll repost.
